The authors present in this publication the edition of the main **Venus tablets** of the period of king Ammizaduga, texts used a basic reference for the chronology of ancient Near Eastern history.  

[These tablets stress the strong connection between the observation of stars and planets, basically a religious activity, and the development of calendars and chronological records in the Ancient Near East.]

